{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:42:18.476150", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- Overall, the network is partially degraded. The 10.1.x.0/24 users and the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) are healthy and reachable end-to-end, including DNS and HTTP load-balanced service web99.local.\\n- The entire 10.2.x.0/24 user side is isolated: hosts there are not receiving DHCP leases and have no IP connectivity to the rest of the network.\\n- Root cause: FRR (OSPF) is stopped on router_core_2, causing loss of OSPF adjacencies and routing for the 10.2.x area behind router_dist_2_1. This breaks DHCP relay and all L3 reachability for 10.2.x.\\n\\nObserved symptoms and impact\\n- Host 10.1.1.0/24 (host_1_1_1_1)\\n  - DHCP lease present: 10.1.1.13/24, default route 10.1.1.1.\\n  - Can ping DNS (10.200.0.2) and load balancer (10.200.0.7).\\n  - HTTP tests:\\n    - http://web99.local returns consistently (total ~1.0–1.1 s).\\n    - http://10.200.0.3 (web_server_0) reachable and responds (total ~1.05–1.14 s).\\n- Host 10.2.1.0/24 (host_2_1_1_1)\\n  - No IP address assigned; routing table empty. It did not obtain a DHCP lease.\\n  - Global reachability matrix shows all 10.2.* hosts have null IPs and “unknown” reachability.\\n- Server and infra health\\n  - DHCP server active and listening on UDP/67; scopes configured for 10.1.x and 10.2.x.\\n  - DNS server listening on 10.200.0.2:53 and reachable from 10.1.x.\\n  - Load balancer listening on TCP/80; default route via 10.200.0.1; reachable from 10.1.x.\\n  - server_access_router has OSPF routes to user subnets and participates in the backbone via 172.16.0.14/31 to router_core_3.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- router_dist_2_1 (10.2.1.1):\\n  - OSPF: “Number of fully adjacent neighbors in this area: 0” (Area 0.0.0.1).\\n  - Routing table: only local 10.2.1.0/24 and its p2p link 172.16.0.10/31; no routes to 10.200.0.0/24 or other networks.\\n  - DHCP relay is running (dhcrelay -i br0 -i eth0 10.200.0.8) but cannot reach 10.200.0.8: “Network is unreachable.”\\n  - L3 link to the core is up (ICMP to 172.16.0.10 works), but no OSPF-learned routes beyond the link.\\n- router_core_2:\\n  - FRR service state: inactive (dead). No OSPF adjacencies, only connected routes (172.16.0.[0/1/4/10/12]/31).\\n  - This device is the only routed neighbor for router_dist_2_1; with FRR down, the 10.2.x area is not participating in OSPF.\\n- router_core_1 and router_core_3:\\n  - OSPF processes are running and have adjacencies. They provide reachability for 10.1.x and 10.200.0.0/24 via the backbone.\\n  - server_access_router OSPF is also healthy with one neighbor (core_3).\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- FRR (OSPF) is not running on router_core_2. This breaks OSPF adjacency with router_dist_2_1, causing the 10.2.x distribution/user area to be disconnected from the OSPF domain.\\n- Consequence: DHCP relay from router_dist_2_1 cannot reach the DHCP server, so hosts in 10.2.x do not obtain leases and remain offline. All 10.2.x subnets lack L3 routing to the server farm and the rest of the network.\\n\\nKey evidence\\n- host_2_1_1_1: no IP, no default route.\\n- Global reachability: all 10.2.* hosts show null IPs and unknown status.\\n- router_dist_2_1 OSPF: “Number of fully adjacent neighbors in this area: 0”; routing table lacks routes to 10.200.0.0/24.\\n- router_dist_2_1 ping to 10.200.0.8: “Network is unreachable”; yet ping to directly connected core peer 172.16.0.10 succeeds.\\n- router_core_2: “frr.service - FRRouting … Active: inactive (dead).”\\n- Working path validation: host_1_1_1_1 successfully pings DNS and load balancer; curl to web99.local returns normally; server_access_router has OSPF routes to 10.1.* and 10.200.0.0/24.\\n\\nAssessment of other design intents\\n- Backend web servers being non-directly reachable from user subnets appears consistent with topology: backend network (20.200.0.0/24 on load_balancer eth1) is not advertised in OSPF; no evidence of user reachability to 20.200.0.0/24.\\n\\nOverall health status\\n- Server farm and 10.1.x user segment: healthy.\\n- 10.2.x user segment: down due to OSPF outage at router_core_2, isolating router_dist_2_1 and breaking DHCP relay and routing., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='e3e4e735-dd76-4154-a3e9-b796d3694aa3'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
